    "description": "Ikegami Tsushinki Co., Ltd. engages in the provision of broadcast equipment in Japan and internationally. The company offers broadcast equipment, including camera systems, digital cameras, HDTV camera systems, camera control units, base station, fiber camera adaptors, OLED and LCD viewfinders, system expanders, control panels, command converters, and mounting plate for studio/control room system, relay/broadcasting system/news gathering equipment, R2 remote production system, and helicopter tv system; medical equipment, such as output and medical grade cameras, LCD monitors, and digital video recorders; inspection equipment, including tablet inspection and printing system, medicine inspection equipment, tablet inspection machine, plane and single sheet visual inspection equipment for checking surface of films, panels, and metal foils; and security camera systems. Ikegami Tsushinki Co., Ltd. was formerly known as Ikegami Tsushinki Seisakusho and changed its name to Ikegami Tsushinki Co., Ltd. in 1951. Ikegami Tsushinki Co., Ltd. was founded in 1946 and is based in Tokyo, Japan."
